li%3ESixteen%20states%20and%20D.C.%20are%20suing%20the%20Trump%20administration%20over%20blocking%20EV%20charger%20funding.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20lawsuit%20targets%20the%20Department%20of%20Transport%20for%20halting%20the%20%245%20billion%20NEVI%20program.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ETesla%20was%20a%20major%20funding%20recipient%2C%20receiving%20%2431%20million%20from%20the%20initiative.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20coalition%20of%2016%20states%20and%20Washington%2C%20D.C.%2C%20filed%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foag.ca.gov%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fattachments%2Fpress-docs%2FCOMPLAINT%2520NEVI.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elawsuit%3C%2Fa%3E%20Wednesday%20against%20the%20Trump%20administration%20for%20suspending%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-halts-major-ev-charger-rollout-that-gave-tesla-funding-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%245%20billion%20electric%20vehicle%20charging%20initiative%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20suit%20targets%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%2C%20Transport%20Secretary%20Sean%20Duffy%2C%20the%20Federal%20Highway%20Administration%2C%20and%20its%20Acting%20Administrator%20Gloria%20M.%20Shepherd%2C%20over%20the%20abrupt%20halt%20of%20the%20National%20Electric%20Vehicle%20Infrastructure%20Formula%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENEVI%20was%20established%20under%20the%202021%20Bipartisan%20Infrastructure%20Law%20and%20was%20a%20central%20component%20of%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20push%20for%20a%20national%20EV%20charging%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20was%20one%20of%20its%20top%20recipients%2C%20receiving%20%2431%20million%20to%20expand%20its%20Supercharger%20network%20in%20partnership%20with%20public%20initiatives%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20an%20executive%20order%20issued%20by%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20on%20his%20first%20day%20back%20in%20office%20directed%20federal%20agencies%20to%20freeze%20funds%20allocated%20by%20the%20Bipartisan%20Infrastructure%20Law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%2C%20backed%20by%20states%20including%20California%20and%20Colorado%2C%20argues%20that%20the%20executive%20branch%20does%20not%20have%20the%20authority%20to%20withhold%20or%20redirect%20the%20funding%2C%20and%20that%20the%20FHWA%20unlawfully%20revoked%20funds%20that%20Congress%20had%20directed%20to%20states%20for%20building%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plaintiffs%20said%20that%20the%20FHWA's%20action%20to%20immediately%20freeze%20more%20than%20%242.7%20billion%20in%20NEVI%20funds%20disrupted%20projects%20already%20under%20contract%20or%20in%20planning%2C%20causing%20long-term%20financial%20and%20logistical%20harm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20criticized%20the%20move%2C%20calling%20it%20%26quot%3Banother%20Trump%20gift%20to%20China.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENewsom%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Binstead%20of%20hawking%20Teslas%20on%20the%20White%20House%20lawn%2C%20President%20Trump%20could%20actually%20help%20Elon%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20nation%20%E2%80%94%20by%20following%20the%20law%20and%20releasing%20this%20bipartisan%20funding.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EColorado%20Attorney%20General%20Phil%20Weiser%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcoag.gov%2Fpress-releases%2Fphil-weiser-sues-trump-federal-electric-vehicle-infrastructure-funding-5-7-25%2F%3Futm_campaign%3DCOAGSproutSocialCampaign%26utm_content%3D1746656530%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_source%3Dfacebook%2Clinkedin%2Ctwitter%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20was%20%26quot%3Bbreaking%20the%20law%26quot%3B%20by%20withholding%20funding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCongress%20had%20the%20foresight%20to%20authorize%20funding%20to%20build%20this%20important%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20it%20must%20be%20restored%20immediately%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20will%20not%20hesitate%20to%20take%20them%20to%20court%20to%20ensure%20they%20follow%20the%20law.%26quot%3B%3C