ating%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20that%20that's%20generally%20a%20good%20way%20for%20founders%20to%20operate.%20If%20you're%20running%20the%20company%20and%20you're%20on%20the%20hook%20for%20everything%20and%20there's%20something%20that's%20important%20at%20whatever%20level%20of%20detail%20in%20the%20organization%2C%20I%20don't%20get%20the%20logic%20of%20saying%20'I'm%20not%20going%20to%20be%20involved%20in%20that.'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BYou%20want%20to%20have%20humility%20and%20know%20that%20if%20you're%20diving%20into%20some%20decision%2C%20you%20may%20not%20have%20the%20most%20context%20immediately%2C%20but%20I%20generally%20think%20that%20you%20want%20to%20be%20able%20to%20just%20have%20the%20cultural%20expectation%20that%20things%20are%20not%20going%20to%20be%20so%20hierarchical%20and%20you're%20just%20going%20to%20dive%20into%20whatever%20you%20want.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22af75846c-d95b-44c2-937a-a375feb64e62%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENo%20recurring%20one-on-one%20meetings%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EZuckerberg%20said%20he%20tries%20to%20minimize%20standing%20meetings%20and%20has%20just%20two%20weekly%20recurring%20meetings%20with%20a%20small%20group.%20One%20is%20an%20open-ended%20strategy%20discussion%2C%20and%20the%20other%20focuses%20on%20company%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20say%20I%20don't%20have%20one-on-ones%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20recurring%20scheduled%20one-on-ones%2C%20I%20talk%20to%20all%20these%20people%20constantly%2C%20more%20than%20they%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20me%20I'm%20sure%2C%20but%20I%20do%20it%20when%20I%20have%20something%20that%20I%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20them%20about%2C%20or%20if%20they%20want%20to%20talk%20to%20me%20I%20try%20to%20generally%20keep%20a%20bunch%20of%20time%20open.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20tries%20to%20ensure%20that%20he%20has%20a%20block%20of%20time%20each%20day%20to%20focus%20on%20key%20tasks%2C