%20for%20longevity%20with%20the%20'Norwegian%20method'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%227547%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20on%20an%20exercise%20bike%20is%20performing%20an%20endurance%20test%20in%20a%20lab%20as%20his%20coach%20looks%20on.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681cb8613fe8d39283654790%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%225031%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EOlav%20Aleksander%20Bu%2C%20left%2C%20is%20a%20renowned%20coach%20to%20elite%20athletes%20such%20as%20Norwegian%20triathlete%20champion%20Kristian%20Blummenfelt%20(right).%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20CORE%2FSantara%20Group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EOlav%20Aleksander%20Bu%20is%20an%20elite%20endurance%20coach%20whose%20training%20balances%20intensity%20for%20better%20results.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYou%20can%20use%20his%20strategies%20for%20better%20VO2%20max%2C%20a%20key%20metric%20of%20fitness%20and%20longevity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EUnderstanding%20factors%20like%20heart%20rate%2C%20threshold%2C%20and%20heat%20can%20help%20you%20work%20out%20smarter.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Olympic%20triathlete%20gold%20medalist%20Kristian%20Blummenfelt%2C%20training%20is%20a%20full-time%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20exercises%20up%20to%2010%20hours%20a%20day%20to%20keep%20his%20heart%20and%20lungs%20in%20peak%20shape%2C%20and%20doubles%20up%20on%20tough%20sessions%20as%20part%20of%20a%20workout%20strategy%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BThe%20Norwegian%20method.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20method%20can%20help%20you%2C%20a%20mere%20mortal%2C%20improve%20your%20own%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flongevity-trainer-fitness-markers-to-watch-for-a-longer-life-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elongevity%20and%20fitness%3C%2Fa%3E%20spending%20just%20a%20fraction%20of%20the%20time%20working%20out%2C%20according%20to%20his%20coach%2C%20Olav%20Aleksander%20Bu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20think%20of%20elite%20athletes%20as%20freaks%20of%20nature.%20In%20reality%2C%20what%20we%20see%20is%20working%20with%20elite%20athletes%20works%20with%20everybody%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider%20in%20an%20interview%20tied%20to%20a%20partnership%20with%20fitness%20tech%20company%20Core.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBu%2C%20who%20has%20coached%20some%20of%20the%20best%20endurance%20athletes%20on%20the%20planet%2C%20uses%20the%20Norwegian%20method%20to%20dial%20in%20workout%20intensity%20while%20avoiding%20injury%20or%20burnout.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20same%20principles%20can%20help%20you%20work%20out%20more%20efficiently.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d7228e9f-c084-420e-a64f-5fa929fcf254%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20Norwegian%20method%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20most%20basic%20level%2C%20the%20Norwegian%20method%20is%20about%20balancing%20volume%20%E2%80%94%20the%20amount%20of%20work%20you're%20doing%20%E2%80%94%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Factive-recovery-strategies-reduce-muscle-soreness-boost-muscle-gains-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecovery%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20key%20principle%20is%20alternating%20periods%20of%20high%20intensity%20with%20periods%20of%20lower%20intensity%20and%20rest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20train%20with%20the%20Norwegian%20method%20for%20a%20higher%20VO2%20max%20(the%20ability%20to%20circulate%20and%20use%20oxygen%20effectively)%20and%20better%20endurance%2C%20you%20need%20the%20right%20kind%20of%20stress%20on%20your%20body%2C%20which%20means%20being%20able%20to%20measure%20intensity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20tired%20you%20feel%20isn't%20necessarily%20an%20accurate%20measure%20of%20how%20hard%20you're%20working%2C%20Bu%20said.%20Pace%20may%20not%20be%20a%20good%20measure%20of%20intensity%20either%20because%20it%20varies%20so%20much%20between%20athletes%2C%20and%20even%20for%20the%20same%20athlete%20under%20different%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERunning%20five%20miles%20in%2040%20minutes%20might%20be%20easy%20for%20the%20pros%20but%20crushingly%20difficult%20for%20a%20newbie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224240%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20shirtless%20athlete%20in%20an%20exercise%20science%20lab%20is%20wearing%20CORE%20heat%20sensors%2C%20assisted%20by%20his%20coach.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681a5684c6ad288d14802e14%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222827%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHeat%20training%20with%20fitness%20tech%20like%20the%20CORE%20sensor%20can%20help%20you%20exercise%20to%20improve%20heart%20health%20and%20VO2%20max%20without%20adding%20stress%20on%20your%20joints%20and%20muscles%2C%20as%20shown%20here%20by%20Bu%20and%20Blummenfelt.%3Cp%3ECORE%20%2F%20Santara%20Group%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20stay%20on%20target%2C%20Bu%20uses%20metrics%20like%20body%20temperature%20and%20lactate%2C%20a%20byproduct%20the%20body%20produces%20during%20intense%20exercise%2C%20to%20precisely%20assess%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-workout-weight-loss-plan-legit-running-coach-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehow%20hard%20athletes%20can%20push%20during%20training%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20you%20can%20buy%20a%20device%20to%20measure%20lactate%2C%20heart%20rate%20can%20also%20measure%20effort%2C%20and%20it's%20easier%20to%20do%20at%20home%20with%20a%20smartwatch%20or%20fitness%20tracker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22728d555f-a960-47dc-ad40-c1a94a058130%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20to%20boost%20your%20VO2%20max%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvo2-max-explained-what-is-good-how-improve-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20sample%20workout%20plan%20to%20increase%20VO2%20max%3C%2Fa%3E%20involves%20three%20sessions%20per%20week%20of%20your%20preferred%20cardio%20exercise%2C%20such%20as%20running%20or%20biking.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou'll%20aim%20to%20spend%20time%20at%20your%20threshold%20heart%20rate%2C%20the%20maximum%20effort%20you'd%20be%20able%20to%20sustain%20for%20about%20an%20hour%20of%20work.%20The%20pros%20test%20their%20threshold%20in%20a%20lab%2C%20but%20you%20can%20estimate%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20popular%20technique%20is%20to%20run%20or%20bike%20hard%20for%2030%20minutes%20and%20record%20your%20average%20heart%20rate%20for%20the%20last%2020%20minutes.%20Your%20threshold%20for%20running%20or%20biking%20may%20be%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20threshold%20sessions%2C%20alternate%20between%20periods%20of%20work%20at%20that%20intensity%20and%20rest%20to%20recover.%20Some%20example%20intervals%20from%20different%20Norwegian%20training%20plans%20include%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFour%20minutes%20of%20hard%20effort%2C%20followed%20by%20three%20minutes%20of%20rest%2C%20repeated%20for%20four%20total%20sets%2C%20popularized%20by%20coach%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ntnu.edu%2Femployees%2Fulrik.wisloff%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUlrik%20Wisl%C3%B8ff%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%2C000-meter%20effort%2C%20followed%20by%20a%20minute%20of%20rest%2C%20repeated%2010%20times%2C%20is%20a%20go-to%20for%20athlete%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mariusbakken.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMarius%20Bakken%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20one%20of%20those%20sessions%2C%20you%20could%20incorporate%20heat%20training%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20Bu's%20favorite%20ways%20to%20get%20the%20right%20workout%20intensity%2C%20both%20in%20his%20own%20workouts%20and%20for%20his%20athletes.%20Adding%20heat%20also%20works%20the%20heart%20and%20lungs%20while%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuild-leg-strength-muscle-without-joint-pain-personal-trainer-tips-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epreventing%20joint%20pain%20during%20exercise%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20be%20most%20precise%20by%20using%20a%20sensor%20to%20monitor%20your%20body%20temperature.%20Aim%20for%20around%20101.3%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%2C%20building%20toward%20102.2%20during%20your%20session%2C%20but%20not%20exceeding%20that%20temperature%2C%20Bu%20said.%20Increase%20the%20heat%20by%20exercising%20in%20warm%20weather%20or%20wearing%20more%20layers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20you%20can%20safely%20challenge%20your%20body%20to%20keep%20getting%20stronger%20by%20gradually%20spending%20more%20time%20at%20that%20threshold%20intensity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20is%20thinking%20long-term.%20Working%20out%20for%20an%20hour%20or%20two%20once%20a%20week%20isn't%20going%20to%20make%20much%20of%20a%20difference%20to%20your%20fitness.%20Progress%20comes%20from%20repeating%20the%20routine%20for%20weeks%20and%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20that%20find%20great%20pleasure%20in%20training%20find%20a%20sustainable%20intensity%2C%20and%20they%20get%20to%20perceive%20the%20tremendous%20effect%20it%20has%20on%20their%20physique%2C%26quot%3B%20Bu%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-vo2-max-norwegian-method-training-elite-coach-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1746699901000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F681cb8b1c6ad288d14805d6d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-vo2-max-norwegian-method-training-elite-coach-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Elite%20coach%20Olav%20Aleksander%20Bu%20has%20trained%20top%20athletes%20with%20the%20Norwegian%20method.%20You%20can%20use%20it%20to%20boost%20your%20own%20V02%20max%20and%20longevity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22glandsverk%40insider.com%20(Gabby%20Landsverk)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-improve-vo2-max-norwegian-method-training-elite-coach-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%